<https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_F4_FS_ProvidesMachineSearch.ttl> a ftr:Metric, dqv:Metric, dcat:Resource ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_F4_FS_ProvidesMachineSearch.ttl"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_F4_FS_ProvidesMachineSearch.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcat:landingPage "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_F4_FS_ProvidesMachineSearch.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcterms:title "FAIR Metric - F4 - Metadata - Resource provides machine search interface"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "FM_F4_FS_ProvidesMachineSearch"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "FM_F4_FS_ProvidesMachineSearch"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:description """**What is being measured?**

This metric evaluates whether the database, standard or policy resource provides a machine-accessible search and/or browse interface. In FAIRsharing, this corresponds to at least one Data Process that includes a Search or Browse function, uses a non-User Interface access method, and supports Read or Read/Write operations. Expected input is the DOI or URL of the registry (e.g. FAIRsharing) record under evaluation.

**Why should we measure it?**

F4 requires that (meta)data are registered or indexed in a searchable resource. Providing a machine-accessible search and/or browse interface enables computational systems to discover content within the resource through automated discovery mechanisms."""^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:keyword "FAIR"^^xsd:string ;
    schema:about "Not applicable"^^xsd:string ;
